The National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) on Monday set up a 5-member committee to review the petitions on anti-party activities by some members from the states. A statement signed by the National Publicity Secretary, Mallam Lanre Issa Onilu, said the Deputy National ChairmanÂ (South), Otunba Niyi Adebayo is Chairman of the Committee. The statement said the NWC has received several petitions alleging various forms of anti-party activities by some members, including working against the party or our candidates in the just concluded elections. Other members are National Vice Chairman (South-west), Mr. Bankole Oluwajana; National Legal Adviser, Babatunde Ogala; National Treasurer, Adamu Fanda and National Disabled Leader, Misbau Lawal Didi. The statement said the Committee has one week to submit its report. 